# trivy baseline ignore file for bi8s-go.

#

# Format: one CVE/Misconfig ID per line, optional `# justification`.

# Scope is repository-wide (filesystem scan via .github/workflows/ci.yml).

#

# Add entries only when:

# - upstream has no fix yet AND mitigation is in place, or

# - finding is not exploitable in our deployment topology.

#

# Re-evaluate on every dependency bump. Empty by default — populate as

# real findings surface in CI.

# --- IaC misconfig accepted by design (mirrors infra/tofu/.tfsec/config.yml) -

# Bucket SSE uses AES256 (SSE-S3) instead of customer-managed KMS keys.

# Cost/complexity tradeoff for a non-regulated workload; same decision as

# aws-s3-encryption-customer-key in tfsec.

AVD-AWS-0132

# CloudFront distribution has no WAF attached. Dev/staging only — prod

# fronts traffic via ALB+WAF; revisit when CDN takes prod traffic.

AVD-AWS-0011

# ECR repository tag mutability is MUTABLE for dev convenience. Prod

# pipelines pin by digest, so mutable tags do not break supply chain.

AVD-AWS-0031

# GitHub OIDC deploy role uses service-level wildcards (s3:_, ec2:_, …).

# Required so a single CI role can manage the full IaC stack; same as

# aws-iam-no-policy-wildcards in tfsec.

AVD-AWS-0345

# Egress 0.0.0.0/0 on app/opensearch SGs. Required for AWS API calls and

# package fetches; ingress is locked down. Standard for private subnets.

AVD-AWS-0104

# S3 public-access-block toggles are wired through `var.block_public_access`.

# All callers pass `true`; trivy cannot follow the variable. False positive.

AVD-AWS-0086
AVD-AWS-0087
AVD-AWS-0091
AVD-AWS-0093

# Public subnets map public IPs on launch. Required for the ALB / NAT

# gateway tier; private subnets host the actual workloads.

AVD-AWS-0164
